title: For Sale:  Glock 20c  10mm GEN 3
postcontent:
The GLOCK 20, in 10mm AUTO, provides nothing short of massive firepower especially suited for hunting. The use of GLOCK hi-tech polymer considerably reduces felt recoil. With muzzle energy of 550 ft/lbs, and a magazine capacity of 15 rounds, this 10mm is your reliable companion on every hunt. The G20 also provides a safe and accurate finishing shot, even when hunting big game.

Package comes with 4 high cap mags and 500 rds. Original case. Only 20rds threw the gun. Also ported barrel 700.00 FIRM CASH NO TRADES



Quick summary of the Pros/Cons for the Glock 20C: 

Pros: 

-Reliable (not a single failure to date) 
-Accurate (more accurate than 99% of the shooters that own one) 
-Durable (10mm Glocks seem to do better than their competition [EAA/1911/ect...] in handling the 10mm wear) 
-Easy to maintain 
-TONS of aftermarket support 
-15+1 capacity 
-Glock's customer service is great 
-Durable finish 
-Cheap replacement parts, should you ever need them 
-Low Bore Axis resulting in a relatively soft shooting gun 
-Easily modified to fit the shooters' preferences 
-Requires very little cleaning/lubrication to run reliably 
-Muzzle flip and perceived recoil are minimized vs the standard G20 allowing for faster follow up shots 


Cons: 

-The C model is much louder 
-The ported barrel may make your front sight turn black (mine doesn't seem to but I've seen others that do it after 2 or 3 rounds) 
-The ported barrel causes a decrease in muzzle velocity 
-The grip is large and may be too large for some shooters to grip properly

title: For Sale:  Sig P229 .40 CPO LNIB
postcontent:
Bought Nov '13 and haven't fired or carried it. Hard to tell if it's ever been fired; No sign of wear or cosmetic blemishes. Looks like a brand new gun. Comes with (2) New 12-Round Sig mags. Will ship For additional $25.

Several people have asked what CPO means. CPO is a term the SIG factory uses to signify "Certified Previously Owned." The SIG factory reconditions certain previously purchased guns and then Certifies that the gun is in excellent, working condition and sold with one year warranty to the new owner. Often times police departments buy batches of SIGs that never see service then trade them in when The dept goes to a different caliber, model or manufacturer. I can't prove it, but suspect that my gun was unfired when turned in.

title: For Sale:  Little Crossbow

Probably good for kids (adult supervision of course) or some screwing around in your back yard.  I wouldn't shoot anything bigger than a dog with this thing and hope to kill it, I have shot it into a couple of trees which ended up putting the bolt a good few inches into it though.  I would definitely not consider this a toy but I also would not shoot at deer with it.  It would probably kill a zombie with a headshot.

I'd say - squirrels, rabbits, cats and toddlers are too small, whereas wolves and large boar are pushing the upper limits of this thing.

title: For Sale:  AR15 Battle Rifle 5.45 x 39 w/ upgrades and ammo
postcontent:
The rifle is a quality AR-15 built with a Spikes Tactical dedicated upper including a Spike’s full-auto BCG.  Barrel has M4 feed ramps, 16 in carbine length 1/8 twist barrel with flash hider and A2 front sight. Rear sight is MBUS flip up style.  The lower is an aluminum forged SAA with a PSA polished lower parts kit. The 5.45 x 39 ammo build allows you to get shooting time at a price far below what you would pay for .223/5.56 ammo.  The ballistics and shooting experience is virtually indistinguishable from a 5.56 chambered AR.  It can be converted to MilSpec 5.56 simply by changing the barrel and the bolt (Bolt carrier is the same).  

Rounding out the build is a Magpul MOE front hand guard and the legendary Magpul UBR telescoping stock.  Google Magpul UBR for details.  They are almost impossible to find for less than $250.

It comes with a (5) ASC 30 round mags dedicated to the 5.45 x 39 round.  You can use std AR15 mags but you have to load them a few rounds short for them to function properly.  The ASCs feed flawlessly at full capacity.  

The price reflects the fact that this is a serious battle rifle built with premium components, not a mall ninja economy model.  I built two of them for my son and me to shoot a few years back a since he will be in Germany for the next 4 years, its time let someone else have some quality trigger time.

Rifle is $850 and I can include about 1000 rounds of recent manufacture 7N6 ammo in a spam can for an extra $175.00.  I have extra 5.45 x 39 ammo if you want more so let me know.
